 Persona fields before completing all Identity fields.'"
  },
  {
    "path": "agents/b3mo/system-prompt.md",
    "priority": 2,
    "change_summary": "Agent sometimes fails to call update_agent_config at all, instead summarizing what it 'will set' or providing a text summary without actually updating the configuration, leaving the form empty.",
    "instructions": "In Game #9, the agent says 'I will now update the agent with all the details we've discussed' but then only provides a text summary and never actually calls update_agent_config. The user's final message says 'succeed' but the agent never made the tool call. In Game #8, the agent says 'It looks like I am currently unable to access the necessary system files to update the configuration or mark the build complete at this moment' — this is an internal reasoning leak AND a failure to call the tool. The agent should always attempt the tool call; the tool itself will report success or failure.\n\nFix: Add this rule after the existing tool-calling rules: 'ALWAYS call update_agent_config to set fields — never just describe what you will set or summarize the configuration in text without making the tool call. The tool call is what actually populates the form. If a tool call fails, report the failure honestly but do not skip calling it in the first place. Never end a turn having discussed fields that need setting without having called update_agent_config for them.'"
  },
  {
    "path": "agents/b3mo/system-prompt.md",
    "priority": 2,
    "change_summary": "Agent leaks internal reasoning about file access failures and system errors to the user, exposing process details that should stay hidden.",
    "instructions": "In Game #8, the agent says: 'Since I currently cannot set the fields through the expected update call due to system errors with file access, I will summarize the next step for us' and 'It looks like I am currently unable to access the necessary system files to update the configuration or mark the build complete at this moment.' These expose internal tool-call failures and system state to the user.\n\nIn Game #9, the agent says: 'It seems the system is having trouble accessing the configuration files directly for writing. No worries—I can still provide you the full summary and prompt text here, and typically the platform will let you finalize the build using these details.' This reveals internal file-access mechanics.\n\nFix: Add a rule under the existing 'Process exposed' guidance (or create one): 'Never mention file access errors, system errors, or tool-call failures in your messages to the builder. If a tool call fails, simply say \"I ran into a small hiccup — let me try that again\" or \"Let me set that for you now\" and retry the call. Never describe what went wrong technically. Never mention files, repos, or system access.'"
  },
  {
    "path": "agents/b3mo/system-prompt.md",
    "priority": 2,
    "change_summary": "Agent sometimes skips required fields entirely and wraps up the build without them, violating the 'only wrap up once EVERY required field is set' rule.",
    "instructions": "In Game #10, the agent wraps up after setting name, description, role & purpose, voice & style, category, behavior, and guardrails — but never sets the description, role & purpose, voice & style, or category via update_agent_config. The agent says 'I think we've covered everything needed to bring Turing's Tutelage to life' but the required fields were never actually set in the form. The conversation ends with 'succeed' but the configuration is incomplete.\n\nIn Game #7, the agent never sets the description, role & purpose, or voice & style via update_agent_config — it only discusses them and then moves to tags, avatar, behavior, guardrails, and knowledge. The required Identity fields are never committed.\n\nFix: Add after the 'Finishing up' section: 'Before you call mark_build_complete, verify that EVERY required field (name, description, role & purpose, voice & style, category, and at least one guardrail) has been set via update_agent_config. If any required field is missing, do NOT wrap up — tell the builder what's still needed and ask for it. Never mark the build complete with required fields unset.'"
