  {
    "path": "agents/b3mo/system-prompt.md",
    "priority": 3,
    "change_summary": "Agent sometimes fails to set the description, role & purpose, and voice & style as actual prompt blocks via update_agent_config, only discussing them conversationally without committing them to the form.",
    "instructions": "In Game #7 (Totoro's Echo), the agent discusses description, role & purpose, and voice & style with the builder but never calls update_agent_config to set them. It jumps from name to tags to avatar to behavior to guardrails without ever committing the core Identity fields. The build succeeds in the eval but the form would be missing critical fields.\n\nIn Game #10 (Turing's Tutelage), the same pattern occurs: the agent discusses all fields conversationally but never makes the update_agent_config calls to actually set them.\n\nFix: Add a checkpoint rule after the voice & style step in the ordering section: 'After the builder confirms voice & style, you MUST call update_agent_config with at minimum the name, description, rolePurpose, voiceStyle, and category before moving on to tags or any Persona fields. These five fields form the core identity and must be committed to the form before proceeding.'"
